      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2022 R2) is commercial software with documented verification test suite and version-controlled release notes. Software QA procedures including regression testing and change control are maintained by the vendor, satisfying MRL 2 requirements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy testing was performed using the method of manufactured solutions on canonical rotating flow benchmarks. Observed spatial order of accuracy of 1.98 is consistent with the second-order discretization scheme employed, confirming correct code implementation."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation-based grid convergence index (GCI) was computed across three systematically refined meshes (2.1 M, 6.8 M, 18.4 M cells). GCI for the normalized index of hemolysis at the worst-case operating point is 3.2%, within the 5% acceptance threshold. Temporal discretization error assessed separately via time-step refinement study."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions from the FDA benchmark dataset are well-documented with controlled fluid properties (glycerol-water blood analog), inlet flow rates measured via ultrasonic flow meter (±1% accuracy), and rotational speed verified by optical tachometer. Test conditions are sufficiently characterized to support model validation."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison metrics including validation metric (E) and model validation uncertainty (Uval) were computed per ASME V&V 20. Velocity field comparisons show mean absolute error of 4.7% relative to PIV measurements. Hemolysis index predictions fall within experimental uncertainty bands at four of five operating points."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "The primary quantity of interest, normalized index of hemolysis (NIH), directly maps to the clinical decision quantity (hemolysis risk ranking across operating conditions). Secondary QoIs including shear stress distribution and exposure time are mechanistically linked to the Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power law used in the model."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities were conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry under operating conditions spanning the intended CPB flow range (3–7 L/min, 2500–3500 RPM). The validation domain overlaps substantially with the intended application space, supporting relevance at MRL 2."
    },
    {
